      "content": "# error names must end with Error and use PascalCase\n\nWhen defining operation errors via `ADD_OPERATION_ERROR`:\n\n- **`code`**: UPPERCASE_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `\"MISSING_ID\"`, `\"ENTRY_NOT_FOUND\"`)\n- **`name`**: PascalCase ending with \"Error\" (e.g., `\"MissingIdError\"`, `\"EntryNotFoundError\"`)\n- **`description`**: Human-readable description of the error condition\n\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": \"ENTRY_NOT_FOUND\",\n  \"name\": \"EntryNotFoundError\",\n  \"description\": \"The referenced entry does not exist in the collection\"\n}\n```\n\nThe \"Error\" suffix is required — the code generator uses it to identify error classes. Error names and IDs must be unique across all operations in the document model.\n\nSince [[error classes in reducers are auto-imported by name reference]], the PascalCase name is what you use in reducer code to throw errors.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
